pts; • examples and illustrative case studies; • summary boxes of key research studies and further reading. Focusing on the experiences of stakeholder groups and the themes of power, legitimacy and rehabilitation, the book concludes with an overview of the future challenges for prisons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978144736542640uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447365440?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447365440423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447365440/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles